-- Norilsk, Rosneft, Tatneft May Be Active Today: Russia Stock Market Preview
-- Denis Maternovsky
-- 2010-06-29T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/norilsk-rosneft-tatneft-may-be-active-today-russia-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based  Micex Index  added 1.2 percent to
1,363.40 in Moscow. The dollar-denominated  RTS Index  gained 1.1
percent to 1,403.42.  
 OAO Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): United Co. Rusal, the world’s
largest aluminium producer and owner of a 25 percent stake in
Russia’s largest mining company, plans to convene an
extraordinary general meeting of Norilsk after Chairman
 Alexander Voloshin , whose candidacy was supported by Rusal, was
dismissed by a shareholders meeting and replaced by  Vasily Titov , deputy head of VTB Group, the company said in a statement
late June 28. Rusal also seeks to initiate legal action to
uphold its interest as a minority shareholder, according to the
e-mailed statement. Norilsk added 1.4 percent to 4,872.79
rubles.  
 OAO Rosneft : (ROSN RX) and  OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil
fell from a seven-week high on speculation that production in
the Gulf of Mexico will be undisrupted by a tropical storm in
the region. The August contract retreated 1 percent to $78.10 a
barrel in New York, retreating from its highest settlement since
May 5. Rosneft, Russia’s largest oil producer, jumped 3.3
percent to 202.97 rubles. Lukoil, Russia’s biggest non-state oil
company, fell 1.1 percent to 1,686.52 rubles.  
 OAO Tatneft  (TATN3 RX): The oil producer based in Russia’s
Tatarstan region agreed to borrow $2 billion from a group of
banks in three-, five- and seven-year installments to finance
its operations, the company said in a regulatory filing. Company
shares added 0.2 percent to 143.06 rubles.  
